Criação do script RODRIGO PU2UJN

/etc/svxlink/script/fan.sh em um serviço que roda automaticamente

Criar pasta Script
sudo mkdir -p /etc/svxlink/script

Colar o script
sudo nano /etc/svxlink/script/fan.sh


Verifique permissões do script
sudo chmod +x /etc/svxlink/script/fan.sh

Teste manualmente para garantir que funciona:
sudo /etc/svxlink/script/fan.sh


#Criar o serviço systemd
#Crie o arquivo de serviço:
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/fan.service

####################################################
[Unit]
Description=Serviço de Controle do Fan do SvxLink
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
ExecStart=/etc/svxlink/script/fan.sh
Restart=on-failure
User=root
WorkingDirectory=/etc/svxlink/script

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

####################################################


Habilitar e iniciar o serviço

sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable fan.service
sudo systemctl start fan.service




Verificar status e logs

sudo systemctl status fan.service
sudo journalctl -u fan.service -f




